                </div>
                <p>Family and friends abroad can instantly recharge your Warid Connection today using ding*. The service is easy to use and currently available online at www.ding.com, via 450,000 retailers across North America, Europe and the Middle East or directly from ding’s P2P partnered mobile operators in the Middle East. </p>
                <h2>Online: </h2>
                <p>Customers worldwide can recharge any Warid number using ding* - just visit www.ding.com or download any of the ding* mobile apps. Simply register for free, by filling in your details online and you will receive a confirmation email immediately to activate your account. On the website, simply enter the mobile number you want to top up and send recharge instantly to any Warid mobile number anywhere in the world using your credit / debit card or Paypal account. </p>
                <h2>P2P (Phone-to-Phone): </h2>
                <p>
                    Customers in the Gulf can directly transfer recharge to any Warid subscriber number from any of ding’s P2P partnered mobile operators – currently available via: Zain Saudi Arabia, Zain Bahrain and Omantel &amp; Renna Mobile Oman. The service is easy and instantaneous:
                    Saudi Arabia – Zain: Customers on the Zain network in Saudi Arabia can simply dial *111# and follow instructions on screen to directly transfer recharge directly to any Warid subscriber number, alternatively customers can send an SMS including the Warid subscriber number to 702747.
                    Bahrain - Zain: Customers on the Zain network in Bahrain can directly transfer airtime to any Warid subscriber number simply by sending an SMS including the Warid subscriber number to 77483.
                    Oman - Omantel: Customers on the Omantel network in Oman can simply dial *404# and follow the instructions on screen to transfer recharge directly to any Warid subscriber number.
                    Oman – Renna: Customers on the Renna Mobile network in Oman can directly transfer airtime to any Warid subscriber number simply by sending an SMS including the Warid subscriber number to 90880.
                </p>
                <h2>Retail: </h2>
                <p>Customers worldwide can also recharge any Warid number from over 450,000 retailers across North America, Europe and the Middle East. The service is currently available in all leading exchange houses and stores via POS terminals and self service kiosks – simply look for the ding* logo and the amount will be transferred immediately!</p>
                <p>You can either avail Warid’s International Top-Up  service or simply click here <a href="https://www.ding.com/countries/asia/pakistan/recharge-warid">https://www.ding.com/countries/asia/pakistan/recharge-warid</a> where you will be re-directed  to Warid’s dedicated onlineTop-Up platform.</p>
                <p>For more information on How to use Top Up on roaming and information on retail destinations, please click the following link:</p>
                <p><a href="http://www.waridtel.com/prepaid/recharge/international-top-up"> http://www.waridtel.com/prepaid/recharge/international-top-up</a></p>
